          <td class="compatible">RX-V3073</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <br>
      <p>CEC allows multiple components in the HDMI signal chain to be controlled by one device.</p>
      <p>The transmission of these control signals is also referred to as Bravia Sync, Viera Link, and Anynet+ by other manufacturers.</p>
      <p><img src="images/cec.jpg" width="100%" alt="CEC"></p>
    </div>
    <h4 class="myheadings">HDMI Device Control &gt;&gt;</h4>
    <div class="thecontent">
    <table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="10" width="100%">
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V375</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V475</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V500D</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V575</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V675</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V775</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V1075</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V2073</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V3073</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <br>
      <p>HDMI Device Control enables operation of third party devices (such as Blu-ray players) via the Yamaha remote control without the need to enter any preset remote control codes.</p>
      <p><img src="images/hdmi-control.jpg" width="100%" alt="HDMI Device Control"></p>
    </div>
    <h4 class="myheadings">Audio Return Channel &gt;&gt;</h4>
    <div class="thecontent">
    <table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="10" width="100%">
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V375</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V475</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V500D</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V575</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V675</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V775</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V1075</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V2073</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V3073</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <br>
      <p>Current flat screen TVs support Audio Return Channel (ARC), this allows the audio signal to be returned to the receiver via a single HDMI cable, eliminating the need for a second digital audio cable.</p>
      <p><img src="images/arc.jpg" width="100%" alt="ARC"></p>
    </div>
    
  </div>
  <div class="one-third column">
    <h4 class="myheadings">HDMI Standby Through &gt;&gt;</h4>
    <div class="thecontent">
    <table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="10" width="100%">
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V375</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V475</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V500D</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V575</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V675</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V775</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V1075</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V2073</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V3073</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <br>
      <p>When the receiver is in standby mode (power off), the Standby Through feature allows HDMI source signals to pass through the receiver to the TV.</p>
      <p>While in Standby Through mode, HDMI inputs can still be changed using the remote control.</p>
      <p align="center"><img src="images/hdmi-standby.jpg" width="246" height="572" alt="HDMI Standby Through"></p>
    </div>
    <h4 class="myheadings">HDMI Fast Switching &gt;&gt;</h4>
    <div class="thecontent">
    <table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="10" width="100%">
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V375</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V475</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V500D</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V575</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V675</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V775</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V1075</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V2073</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V3073</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <br>
      <p>HDMI fast switching is found on all of Yamaha’s ’75 Series receivers and provides a quicker transition between HDMI inputs by streamlining the HDMI connection process.</p>
      <p><img src="images/hdmi-fast-switch.jpg" width="100%" alt="HDMI Fast Switching"></p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="one-third column">
    <h4 class="myheadings">Mobile High-Definition Link (MHL) &gt;&gt;</h4>
    <div class="thecontent">
    <table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="10" width="100%">
        <tr>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V375</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V475</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V500D</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V575</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V675</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V775</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V1075</td>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V2073</td>
          <td class="incompatible">RX-V3073</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <br>
      <p>Mobile High-definition Link (MHL) is a new interface standard between mobile devices and products such as televisions and AV receivers.</p>
      <p>MHL allows the transfer of high-definition audio and video from a mobile device (such as a Samsung Galaxy smartphone) to an AV receiver.</p>
      <p><img src="images/mhl.jpg" width="100%" ></p>
    </div>
    <h4 class="myheadings">Lip Sync &gt;&gt;</h4>
    <div class="thecontent">
    <table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="10" width="100%">
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V375</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V475</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V500D</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V575</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V675</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V775</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V1075</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V2073</td>
          <td class="compatible">RX-V3073</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <br>
      <p>Lip Sync refers to the timing of audio when compared to the video signal. There is often more data being transferred through video than audio, which can cause a delay in the video reaching the viewer.</p>
      <p>The result is words being heard before the actors lips have moved! Lip Sync ensures the audio and video are in ‘sync’ by delaying the audio to coincide with the video.</p>
      <p><img src="images/lip-sync.jpg" width="100%" ></p>
